Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.37,0:07:21.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}由于加州最近的灾难\N{\rEng}{\i1}Well, with what happened in California,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:24.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}内华达州现在是全美人口最多的州\N{\rEng}{\i1}that officially makes Nevada one of the most populous states in the Union now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.76,0:07:26.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}但需要强调的是...\N{\rEng}{\i1}The thing that must be said here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:29.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,菲莉西娅·戈登是市立医院的护士\N{\rEng}Felicia Gordon is a nurse at City General.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:35.36,Default-3,,0,0,33,,最近几周她却更像是名收殓员\N{\rEng}Though for the last few weeks, she's felt more like an undertaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:39.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,自夏末以来员工就不断的辞职\N{\rEng}The staff, whose numbers have been dwindling since late summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:44.84,Default-3,,0,0,33,,大家给自己起名叫“自杀小队”\N{\rEng}have begun referring to themselves as the Suicide Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:45.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}稍事休息\N{\rEng}{\i1}We'll be back to talk more about this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.83,0:07:51.52,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}稍后将带来中西部大火和缺水的最新情况\N{\rEng}{\i1}and, uh, also about the fires in the Midwest, speaking of water scarcity, back after this break.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:08:01.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}感谢查尔斯·查克·克兰兹39年来的峥嵘岁月\N{\rEng}{\i1}We'd like to say thank you to Charles Krantz for 39 great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.80,0:08:04.04,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}谢谢你 查克\N{\rEng}{\i1}Thanks, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.94,0:08:08.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.20,0:08:10.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说你又救了一个？\N{\rEng}Heard you got another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.46,0:08:12.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嗯 又一个\N{\rEng}Yeah. One more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:15.27,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我的没那么幸运 手腕都割烂了 你懂的\N{\rEng}Mine wasn't so lucky. Slit wrists, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.29,0:08:17.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,真没办法了\N{\rEng}what were we supposed to do really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.34,0:08:18.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说玛丽露的事了吗？\N{\rEng}Hear about Marilou?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.04,0:08:20.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没 怎么了？\N{\rEng}No. What about Marilou?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.78,0:08:21.91,Default-3,,0,0,33,,她不干了\N{\rEng}She left!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:24.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-还记得她前任佩德罗吗？ -记得\N{\rEng}-Her ex. Remember Pedro? -Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:26.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他冒出来 嘟囔了几句\N{\rEng}He showed up, and I don't know what he said to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:29.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,两人牵着手就走了\N{\rEng}but she walked out holding his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.22,0:08:30.94,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他们离婚离的有多难熬\N{\rEng}And I remember how bad that divorce was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:32.66,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-有印象吗？ -嗯 记得\N{\rEng}-Do you remember? -Yeah, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.74,0:08:36.99,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好吧 往事如烟了 他们又拉上了手\N{\rEng}Well, I guess that's all bridge water 'cause off she went.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.36,0:08:37.80,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an9\i1}...地陷不断出现\N{\rEng}{\i1}...sinkholes that have been opening up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:39.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,现在婚姻都咋样？\N{\rEng}I wonder what the stats are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.36,0:08:43.74,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是分居多还是复合多？\N{\rEng}You think more people are splitting up or getting back together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:46.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是结婚多还是离婚多？\N{\rEng}I mean, do you think marriage rates are up or divorce rates...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.10,0:08:47.77,Default-3,,0,0,33,,结婚多\N{\rEng}Marriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:50.00,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-你是个乐天派 -不\N{\rEng}-You're an optimist. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:53.70,Default-3,,0,0,33,,离婚周期长 没人会去排这个队\N{\rEng}Divorce takes way longer, and I don't think anyone's filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:56.92,Default-3,,0,0,33,,填文件就得半年多 何苦呢？\N{\rEng}Why bother? Six months of paperwork at least. Probably more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.94,0:09:00.43,Default-3,,0,0,33,,结婚领证上下只要一小时\N{\rEng}Marriage license is one page and it takes an hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:03.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,所以我猜结婚多\N{\rEng}I'm gonna guess marriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.69,0:09:05.22,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}午餐不见你 晚餐也不在\N{\rEng}{\i1}Missed you for lunch, missed you for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:09.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(340,46)\fs13}【电影《封面女郎》(1944)】
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.30,0:09:06.87,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}怎么了？辟谷了吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}What's the matter? Don't you eat anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.95,0:09:08.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}好吧 我不饿\N{\rEng}{\i1}Well, I wasn't hungry tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:10.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}那你今早也不饿吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}Weren't you hungry this morning either?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.26,0:09:14.49,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}谁拿了我的舞蹈袜？天哪 谁那么坏\N{\rEng}{\i1}Who stole my nylons? Egads! The very...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:13.18,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(99,76)\frz22\fs9\b1\1c&HAFB349&}菲莉西娅·戈登来电
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:15.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}不饿\N{\rEng}{\i1}Not very.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.27,0:09:17.50,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}昨晚排练到很晚吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}Too much rehearsal last night, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:18.94,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}就像锻炼一样\N{\rEng}{\i1}It was kind of a workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.96,0:09:20.73,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}赖床了？所以今早来的那么晚\N{\rEng}{\i1}That why you slept late?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.76,0:09:21.76,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}我可没晚起\N{\rEng}{\i1}Oh, I didn't sleep late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:22.99,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}我去了上城区\N{\rEng}{\i1}I went uptown.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.01,0:09:25.30,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\an7\i1}-去购物？ -不是\N{\rEng}{\i1}-Shopping? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:28.71,Default-3,,0,0,33,,喂\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:31.87,Default-3,,0,0,33,,喂\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.33,0:09:35.77,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你给挂了？\N{\rEng}You hung up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.85,0:09:37.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:40.40,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但后来想你看的到 所以又...\N{\rEng}But then I figured you probably saw it. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:43.03,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还好吗？\N{\rEng}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:45.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还行吧\N{\rEng}I'm okay, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:46.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你呢？\N{\rEng}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.47,0:09:50.65,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我上班时想到你了\N{\rEng}I was, um, thinking about you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.68,0:09:54.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,当时在猜结婚多还是离婚多\N{\rEng}We were at work talking about marriages and divorces. Like, which are happening more now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:56.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我赌结婚多\N{\rEng}Marriages, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.65,0:09:58.84,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没人愿意等离婚\N{\rEng}Ain't nobody waiting on a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.27,0:10:01.47,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那么再婚呢？\N{\rEng}What about remarriages?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:04.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要约炮得先请我喝酒\N{\rEng}You want to buy a guy a drink first or...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:05.77,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我打赌人们都在复合\N{\rEng}I bet those are happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:07.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这很有意义\N{\rEng}I mean, it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.71,0:10:13.15,Default-3,,0,0,33,,人们现在渴望慰藉和熟悉的事物\N{\rEng}People wanting something comforting and familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.98,0:10:16.76,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那么 你今天过得怎么样？\N{\rEng}So... how was your day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.29,0:10:19.74,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你想复合的意图太明显了 不觉得吗？\N{\rEng}You're just going right for it, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:21.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,陪我聊聊\N{\rEng}Humor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:26.99,Default-3,,0,0,33,,呃 今天就那样\N{\rEng}It was, um...It was a day, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.08,0:10:29.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,有点怪\N{\rEng}You know? Weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.21,0:10:34.35,Default-3,,0,0,33,,家长会开的就像对牛弹琴\N{\rEng}Parent-teacher sessions, felt like pissing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:36.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你听说加州的事儿了吧？\N{\rEng}You know about California, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:37.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说了\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:39.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我听说大部分人都迁移了\N{\rEng}I know they're saying most of it was already evacuated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:42.94,Default-3,,0,0,33,,今天就有几十万灾民东迁\N{\rEng}but I heard today there are hundreds of thousands of refugees trekking east.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.96,0:10:45.73,Default-3,,0,0,33,,知道现在内华达州是全美人口最多的州吗？\N{\rEng}Did you know Nevada is one of the most  populous states in the Union now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.75,0:10:50.71,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听国家电台科学家说 加州就跟烂墙皮一样往下掉\N{\rEng}I heard a, a scientist on NPR say California is peeling away like old wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:53.90,Default-3,,0,0,33,,今天下午 日本又有一座核电站被淹\N{\rEng}And another Japanese reactor got inundated this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.93,0:10:56.22,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他们虽说 停机了 一切安全\N{\rEng}And they're saying, you know, it was shut down and all's well,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.24,0:10:58.19,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但我就是没法相信\N{\rEng}but I just, I, I don't think I believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:11:00.41,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你真是个怀疑论者\N{\rEng}Cynic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:03.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好吧 马蒂 这日子就是这么不靠谱\N{\rEng}Well, we're living in cynical times, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.36,0:11:06.01,Default-3,,0,0,33,,不少人都认为天要塌了\N{\rEng}I mean, some people think we're living in the last times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:08.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,不再是邪教成员这样想了\N{\rEng}Not just the religious crazies either. Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.20,0:11:14.28,Default-3,,0,0,33,,市立医院自杀小队的许多专家也这样说\N{\rEng}And you are hearing that from a member in good standing of the City General Suicide Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.30,0:11:15.58,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那是我们的自称\N{\rEng}That's what we call ourselves now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:17.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,可没瞎说\N{\rEng}No lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:21.89,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\rNote\fs12}用于抢救吞药自尽{\r}\N今天有6人没挺过来 但救回了18人 主要用{\u1}纳洛酮{\u0}\N{\rEng}We lost six today, but there's 18 more we dragged back, mostly with {\u1}naloxone{\u0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:23.50,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但这种药已经供不上了\N{\rEng}But supplies of that are getting very thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.52,0:11:28.40,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我听药房说最多坚持到月底\N{\rEng}And I heard the head pharmacist say we might be completely out by the end of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.88,0:11:30.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,太倒霉了\N{\rEng}That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.36,0:11:32.10,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊 是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:36.03,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是的 太倒霉了 真的太倒霉了\N{\rEng}Yeah, that sucks. It, it really sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.23,0:11:40.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,互联网瘫痪 加州下沉\N{\rEng}The internet's down, and California's hanging by a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.50,0:11:43.65,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还有大火 饥荒 疫情和各种灾难\N{\rEng}There's fires and famines and plagues and all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.67,0:11:47.49,Default-3,,0,0,33,,连我们医院也快崩溃了\N{\rEng}I mean, it just the center doesn't hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:51.38,Default-3,,0,0,33,,有完没完\N{\rEng}It just won't let up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:56.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那天还有多久？\N{\rEng}How long is this gonna go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:11:59.41,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那之前还能撑多久？\N{\rEng}How much can we take before the whole thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:02.66,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我是说 天塌下来前\N{\rEng}before the whole thing goes apart, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.80,0:12:11.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\rNote\fs12}卡尔·萨根是知名的美国天文学家{\r}\N我在教孩子们{\u1}卡尔·萨根{\u0}的理论\N{\rEng}I'm teaching the kids {\u1}Carl Sagan{\u0} right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:14.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你听说过他的宇宙历年法吗？\N{\rEng}You ever hear what he said about the cosmic calendar?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:18.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,呃 想不起来 应该没听过\N{\rEng}Uh... I don't know. I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:21.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你知道 宇宙已有150亿年历史\N{\rEng}Well, the universe is 15 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:26.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,如果你把这150亿年\N{\rEng}And if you took all of that all, all 15 billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.33,0:12:30.40,Default-3,,0,0,33,,都给它压缩到365天的日历中\N{\rEng}and compress them into a single calendar year,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.42,0:12:34.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那么宇宙大爆炸发生在1月1日第一秒\N{\rEng}then the Big Bang happens in the first second, January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.49,0:12:34.04,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}一    月    份
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.25,0:12:36.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,而如今\N{\rEng}And, and today,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.60,0:12:43.82,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们正处于12月31日 最后一天的最后一刻\N{\rEng}oh, right now, we're in the final millisecond of the last minute of the last day, December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.60,0:12:37.44,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}十 二 月 份
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:45.76,Default-3,,0,0,33,,回到起点\N{\rEng}But if you go back to the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.78,0:12:51.11,Default-3,,0,0,33,,回到大爆炸发生的1月1日夜里\N{\rEng}if the, if the Big Bang happens at midnight, January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.13,0:12:55.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,日历里每个月等于12.5亿年\N{\rEng}then each month of this calendar is one and a quarter billion years long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.22,0:12:57.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嘿 别考我数学\N{\rEng}Hey, nobody told me there was math on this exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.53,0:13:00.21,Default-3,,0,0,33,,宇宙在1月1日诞生\N{\rEng}The universe starts January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.23,0:13:04.90,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但此时我们的银河系还没形成 形成要到5月\N{\rEng}but the, uh, the Milky Way didn't form until May.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.23,0:13:04.54,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(138,146)\fs13\1c00222222\b1}五月份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:10.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们的太阳和地球 要到9月中旬才形成\N{\rEng}Our sun and our earth, they don't show up until mid-September.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.01,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}九   月   份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:13.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,生命不久后就有了 但没轮到我们\N{\rEng}Life appears soon after. But not us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.46,0:13:16.57,Default-3,,0,0,33,,猜猜我们什么时候出现的？\N{\rEng}No. No, no, we don't appear for guess how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.59,0:13:18.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,再说一遍 今天不考数学\N{\rEng}Again, I was told there'd be no math.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:21.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,在12月31日\N{\rEng}December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.12,0:13:22.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,出现在日历上的最后一天\N{\rEng}Last day on the calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:22.75,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}十 二 月 份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.77,0:13:29.31,Default-3,,0,0,33,,最早的人类出现在晚上10点半左右\N{\rEng}and the very first human beings on Earth made their debut around 10:30 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:32.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,出现在最后一天的晚上10点半\N{\rEng}10:30 p.m. on the last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.83,0:13:37.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,每一分钟代表着3万年\N{\rEng}And, um, every minute since then is 30,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.22,0:13:46.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,晚上11:46 距离午夜14分钟 人类才学会用火\N{\rEng}So, 11:46 p.m., only 14 minutes ago, humanity tamed fire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:50.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,在距离午夜只剩几秒钟时\N{\rEng}and now we're out of minutes, we're into seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:52.83,Default-3,,0,0,33,,到11点59分20秒\N{\rEng}11:59 and 20 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.85,0:14:00.92,Default-3,,0,0,33,,动植物才被驯化 人类刚开始能制造工具\N{\rEng}the domestication of plants and animals begin, an application for the human talent for making tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:04.27,Default-3,,0,0,33,,到11点59分35秒\N{\rEng}11:59 and 35 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:10.06,Default-3,,0,0,33,,农耕社区演变为首批城市雏形\N{\rEng}agricultural communities evolved into the first cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.08,0:14:12.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们记载的所有历史\N{\rEng}Our recorded history,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.04,0:14:14.76,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说过的所有人\N{\rEng}everyone we've ever heard of,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.78,0:14:24.45,Default-3,,0,0,33,,所有历史书上的事 都只发生在最后10秒钟里\N{\rEng}every single thing in any one of our history books happens in the last 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.49,0:14:32.41,Default-3,,0,0,33,,所有事都集中在最后一天最后一分钟的最后十秒\N{\rEng}The last 10 seconds of the last minute of the last day on the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.41,0:14:35.62,Default-3,,0,0,33,,日历的最后一天\N{\rEng}December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.85,0:14:41.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,该怎么回答你那天还有多久？\N{\rEng}So how long is it gonna go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.55,0:14:43.70,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我不知道 小菲\N{\rEng}I don't know, Fel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:48.14,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要是你说得对 很可能真是这样\N{\rEng}If you're right, and you might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.16,0:14:52.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这可能就是末世 宇宙正在消亡\N{\rEng}that this really is the, the last times and the universe is dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:53.67,Default-3,,0,0,33,,就算它在快速消亡\N{\rEng}and let's just say it's a fast death,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.69,0:14:59.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,即使这一切都发生在最后一秒\N{\rEng}even if all of this is happening in the, the last split second,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:15:00.98,Default-3,,0,0,33,,最后一微秒\N{\rEng}microsecond,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.00,0:15:03.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,谁知道对我们来说是多久\N{\rEng}who knows how long that'll last.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:06.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许是几秒钟 也可以是无限长\N{\rEng}Maybe seconds, maybe eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.44,0:15:12.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许发生在宇宙吐出最后一口气的时候\N{\rEng}Maybe all this is happening as the cosmos burps out its last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.88,0:15:21.55,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许发生在宇宙最后一次心跳的时候\N{\rEng}Maybe it's all happening in the last single solitary heartbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:25.94,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你真能说 马蒂\N{\rEng}Jesus, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:28.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是吧\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.73,0:15:37.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好了 小菲 我该挂了 我...\N{\rEng}Listen, Fel, I should go. I've, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:42.12,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还得批改试卷呢\N{\rEng}I've got tests to grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.65,0:15:44.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,马蒂\N{\rEng}Marty...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.61,0:15:48.64,Default-3,,0,0,33,,一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉\N{\rEng}the world is going down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.66,0:15:52.58,Default-3,,0,0,33,,说不定谁都躲不掉这劫\N{\rEng}So, maybe we're going down the drain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:15:54.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,说不定\N{\rEng}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.45,0:15:56.73,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说了吗 查克·克兰兹要退休了\N{\rEng}But, you know, Chuck Krantz is retiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:16:01.13,Default-3,,0,0,33,,都要天塌下来了 还有这个插曲\N{\rEng}So...I guess there's a gleam of light in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.15,0:16:02.76,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说了 39个峥嵘岁月\N{\rEng}Yes. Thirty-nine great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:04.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,哦 你也看到那个奇葩的广告牌了？\N{\rEng}Oh, you saw that weird billboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:06.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,不 是从收音机里听到的广告\N{\rEng}No, it was an ad on the radio that, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.46,0:16:08.35,Default-3,,0,0,33,,之前跟你讲的那个国家电台\N{\rEng}that NPR show I was telling you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.37,0:16:11.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,国资电台都开始打广告了 这真是世界末日了\N{\rEng}If they're running ads on NPR, it really is the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:15.62,Default-3,,0,0,33,,在这个乱世他还怎么算广告覆盖率\N{\rEng}Tell me, how does Chuck Krantz rate this kind of coverage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.64,0:16:18.15,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我是说 他像个会计师\N{\rEng}I mean... looks like an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.17,0:16:20.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我从没听说过他\N{\rEng}I've never heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.39,0:16:22.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,广告一定用了张老照片\N{\rEng}Used an old photo too, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:26.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他看着都不到40 咋来的40年工龄\N{\rEng}I mean, the guy barely looks 40 at all, let alone 40 years on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.44,0:16:28.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,无奇不有\N{\rEng}The world is full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:33.03,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嘿 马蒂 别喝烈酒了\N{\rEng}And, hey, no hard stuff, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.05,0:16:36.47,Default-3,,0,0,33,,喝点啤酒吧\N{\rEng}Okay? Have a beer instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:38.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,遵命\N{\rEng}You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.15,0:16:47.37,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\i1}俄州环保局对克利夫兰一带下达了空气红色警报\N{\rEng}{\i1}The Ohio EPA has now issued a code red air quality alert for Cleveland and its surrounding...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.13,0:16:47.36,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(203,181)\fs8.5\b1\shad0.5\bord0.5}俄州山火蔓延 克利夫兰居民紧急疏散
