Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.22,0:17:10.81,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,142)\fsp4\shad0.5\bord0.5\fs12\1c00444444}信号中断
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.92,0:17:15.58,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我勒个去\N{\rEng}Shit on a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:26.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\i1}感谢查尔斯·查克·克兰兹39年来的峥嵘岁月\N{\rEng}{\i1}We'd like to say thank you to Charles Krantz for 39 great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:23.10,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(156,98)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H7B4A0C&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.24,0:17:27.80,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\i1}谢谢你 查克\N{\rEng}{\i1}Thanks, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:35.45,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(156,98,156,88)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H7B4A0C&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:35.45,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(162,164)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&HC5D6C0&\b1}39个{\u1}峥嵘{\u0}岁月！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:35.45,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(168,200)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&HC5D6C0&\b1}谢谢你\N查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.50,0:17:37.65,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,142)\fsp4\shad0.5\bord0.5\fs12\1c00444444}信号中断
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.44,0:17:56.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,格斯\N{\rEng}Gus!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.61,0:17:59.66,Default-3,,0,0,33,,哦 嘿 马蒂\N{\rEng}Oh. Hey, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:01.97,Default-3,,0,0,33,,怎么不开车了？\N{\rEng}Where's your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:07.30,Default-3,,0,0,33,,车 车停在半山腰了 好几百辆车都扔路上了\N{\rEng}It's... it's on, it's on the sidewalk halfway down Main Street Hill with a hundred others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.32,0:18:08.87,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我只好步行\N{\rEng}I finally just had to turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:10.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,该死 我走了\N{\rEng}Fuck it, I walked...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:12.22,Default-3,,0,0,33,,猜我走了多远？ 这有五公里了吧？\N{\rEng}What do you think it is, like, three miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.24,0:18:14.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我走了将近五公里\N{\rEng}I just walked three miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.20,0:18:16.39,Default-3,,0,0,33,,哦 你是这要去学校吧 等下\N{\rEng}Oh, you're going to school. Hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.41,0:18:20.22,Default-3,,0,0,33,,呃 我想下 你得绕 你得绕\N{\rEng}Uh, real quick, you gotta, you gotta go,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:22.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你得绕道走11号公路\N{\rEng}listen to me, you gotta go out Route 11
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:24.58,Default-3,,0,0,33,,然后在转到19号公路\N{\rEng}and then hook back on, on, on 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.60,0:18:26.84,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是呀 路上会很堵\N{\rEng}Yeah. There's gonna be plenty of traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:28.32,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你大概得绕至少30公里\N{\rEng}You gotta go out at least 20 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.34,0:18:29.80,Default-3,,0,0,33,,运气好中午能到\N{\rEng}You might make it before lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:32.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-别指望早到 -发生了什么事？\N{\rEng}-I wouldn't count on it. -What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:34.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,市场街和主街交叉那有大地坑\N{\rEng}Giant sinkhole opened up on Market and Main.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:36.55,Default-3,,0,0,33,,老兄 陷得太大了\N{\rEng}Man, the-the thing, it, uh, it's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:38.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要么是降雨导致的\N{\rEng}All the rain probably had something to do with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.83,0:18:40.59,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要么是缺乏维护\N{\rEng}lack of maintenance maybe more so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.61,0:18:42.90,Default-3,,0,0,33,,至少轮不到我去修\N{\rEng}But it's not my department, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.92,0:18:46.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但是 坑下面得有二十多辆车吧\N{\rEng}But, yeah, there's, there's gotta be 20 cars at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.97,0:18:50.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那些车里的人 永远上不来了\N{\rEng}And some of the people in some of those cars, they ain't comin' back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:53.21,Default-3,,0,0,33,,老天 我昨天下班就堵在那里\N{\rEng}Jesus, I was, I was just there last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:54.74,Default-3,,0,0,33,,堵在那好久\N{\rEng}backed up in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:57.52,Default-3,,0,0,33,,幸好你今早不在那里\N{\rEng}Thank God you weren't there this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.54,0:19:00.13,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说加州的事了吧\N{\rEng}I assume you know about California.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:01.83,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我今早没看电视\N{\rEng}I didn't turn on the TV this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.85,0:19:03.05,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-难怪 -有什么新闻吗？\N{\rEng}-Oh! -Is there something new?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:06.01,Default-3,,0,0,33,,都沉下去了\N{\rEng}The, the rest of it went.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.03,0:19:09.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,电视说北加州20%还尚存\N{\rEng}I-I mean, th-they're saying that 20% of Northern California is hanging in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.55,0:19:11.32,Default-3,,0,0,33,,实际也许还剩10%\N{\rEng}which probably means, what, 10%?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.34,0:19:15.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但是粮食产区都没了\N{\rEng}But the food-producing regions are... they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.43,0:19:17.19,Default-3,,0,0,33,,中西部被烧成个焦土\N{\rEng}And with the Midwest turning to charcoal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.21,0:19:18.89,Default-3,,0,0,33,,佛州又被水淹\N{\rEng}and Florida flooding, that's like
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.91,0:19:23.37,Default-3,,0,0,33,,全国粮仓都没了\N{\rEng}all the food-producing regions in the country just gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:24.77,Default-3,,0,0,33,,欧洲的情况也差不多\N{\rEng}And the same thing with Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.79,0:19:26.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,亚洲也在闹饥荒\N{\rEng}I mean, it's famine time in Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:27.77,Default-3,,0,0,33,,听说那死了一百万人\N{\rEng}There's a million people dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.79,0:19:29.37,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他们管它叫做 树...树疫\N{\rEng}They're saying it's the bub-bublonic,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.39,0:19:30.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-树疫病 -鼠疫\N{\rEng}-bubonic plague. -Bubonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:32.56,Default-3,,0,0,33,,对 鼠...鼠疫\N{\rEng}Bu-Bubonic plague. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.58,0:19:34.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还有蜜蜂 十多年前就不正常\N{\rEng}And the bees, I mean, they were in trouble a decade ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.88,0:19:36.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但现在所有蜜蜂都没了\N{\rEng}but they're completely gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:39.04,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许南美洲还有几个蜂巢吧\N{\rEng}I mean, there's a couple of hives or whatever down in South America,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.06,0:19:40.96,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但不产蜂蜜\N{\rEng}but there ain't no honey, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.98,0:19:44.74,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没有这些小虫虫 怎么给剩下的庄稼授粉呢\N{\rEng}And without those little guys, like, what's gonna pollinate all the crops we have left?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:45.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要我说 我可...\N{\rEng}I mean, I can't do...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.81,0:19:47.14,Default-3,,0,0,33,,先打住 稍后聊\N{\rEng}Excuse me. One sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.16,0:19:48.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,哦 哦 好\N{\rEng}Yeah, yeah. That's-that's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.46,0:19:50.31,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是 安 安德莉娅吗？\N{\rEng}A-Andrea? Are you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:52.19,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你是中西部信托银行的安德莉娅吗？\N{\rEng}are you Andrea from Midwest Trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:54.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我是菲莉西娅·安德森的丈夫\N{\rEng}I'm Felicia Anderson's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:56.41,Default-3,,0,0,33,,实际上 是前夫\N{\rEng}Ex, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.43,0:19:57.93,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我觉得你和小菲互相认识\N{\rEng}I think you and Fel know each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.95,0:19:59.72,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们之前在大卫家聚会时见过\N{\rEng}We met at a, a, a game night at David's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.75,0:20:00.83,Default-3,,0,0,33,,几晚游戏聚会\N{\rEng}A few game nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:02.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,对 记得\N{\rEng}Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.22,0:20:03.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你想干什么？\N{\rEng}What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:06.07,Default-3,,0,0,33,,车堵在路上 我刚走了半天\N{\rEng}I just had a long walk, and my car is stuck,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.09,0:20:10.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,而银行 斜了\N{\rEng}and the bank is, it's leaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:11.83,Default-3,,0,0,33,,斜了？\N{\rEng}Leaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.01,0:20:13.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是的\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.53,0:20:16.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,银行就在地坑旁边\N{\rEng}It's on the edge of the sinkhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.45,0:20:17.99,Default-3,,0,0,33,,估计我的职业生涯到此为止\N{\rEng}Guess that's the end of my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.01,0:20:21.17,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嘿 你们银行上头那广告牌是啥意思\N{\rEng}Hey, I'm curious about the billboard on the bank building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.19,0:20:22.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-你看到了吗？ -怎么能躲得过？\N{\rEng}-Have you seen it? -How could I miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.50,0:20:25.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那广告还出现在电视上\N{\rEng}And I saw the ads too, on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.89,0:20:28.21,Default-3,,0,0,33,,电视不再播卖车卖家具的广告了\N{\rEng}No more ads for cars or discount furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:32.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,只播“感谢查尔斯·克兰兹39年来的峥嵘岁月 谢谢你 查克”\N{\rEng}Just, "Charles Krantz, 39 great years. Thanks, Chuck."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.64,0:20:34.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他不是你银行的人？\N{\rEng}So, he doesn't work at the bank?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.55,0:20:37.40,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他不是从你银行退休？\N{\rEng}He's not retiring from the bank?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:40.10,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我根本不认识这个人\N{\rEng}I don't know Charles Krantz.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.12,0:20:44.93,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我觉得这就是个恶搞 玩行为艺术\N{\rEng}I think it's just a prank. Performance art.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.95,0:20:46.51,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你保重\N{\rEng}Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.83,0:20:55.51,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他们看起来像是灾民\N{\rEng}They look like refugees.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.53,0:20:56.71,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:01.39,Default-3,,0,0,33,,至少大家不再惊慌失措了\N{\rEng}No one looks that concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.41,0:21:03.17,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那又怎样？\N{\rEng}What good would that do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.19,0:21:05.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,刚开始大家都惊慌失措\N{\rEng}All was concerned at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.71,0:21:07.52,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还记得那些抗议吗？\N{\rEng}Remember the protests?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.54,0:21:09.39,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还记得他们推倒白宫的围栏吗？\N{\rEng}You remember they knocked over the fence at the White House,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.41,0:21:11.31,Default-3,,0,0,33,,记得他们向那些学生开枪吗？\N{\rEng}and all those students got shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.33,0:21:13.05,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-是的 -还有俄罗斯政府被推翻\N{\rEng}-Yeah. -And the overthrow of the Russian government.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.07,0:21:15.66,Default-3,,0,0,33,,巴基斯坦和印度间的四日战争\N{\rEng}You got the Four Day War between Pakistan and India
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:20.97,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还有他妈的德国火山喷发\N{\rEng}and the fucking... the volcano in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.99,0:21:24.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,德国火山还能喷发 太扯了\N{\rEng}There was a volcano in Germany. That's, that's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:26.98,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们自我安慰 一切都会过去的\N{\rEng}And we just kept saying, "Oh, it's gonna blow over."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.00,0:21:30.69,Default-3,,0,0,33,,看来过不去的 对吧？\N{\rEng}That doesn't look to be happening, though, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:33.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.48,0:21:37.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我觉得自杀的人最终会减少\N{\rEng}I think that suicides will slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.35,0:21:42.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我觉得人们最终会等待\N{\rEng}I think people will just...wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.93,0:21:46.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,等什么？\N{\rEng}For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.10,0:21:48.15,Default-3,,0,0,33,,等结局\N{\rEng}The end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:53.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,万物的大结局\N{\rEng}This is the end of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:56.11,Default-3,,0,0,33,,{\rNote\fs10}库伯勒-罗丝悲伤模型五阶段：否认 愤怒 恳求 沮丧 接受{\r}\N我们正处在{\u1}悲伤模型{\u0}第五阶段\N{\rEng}I mean, we're, we're going through {\u1}the five stages of grief{\u0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.11,0:22:00.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你明白吗？我们到了最后阶段\N{\rEng}Don't you get it? I mean, we just, we just landed on the final stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.46,0:22:02.50,Default-3,,0,0,33,,接受\N{\rEng}Acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.60,0:22:10.38,Default-3,,0,0,33,,等待 才是最难熬的\N{\rEng}The waiting...I think that's the hardest part.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.74,0:22:13.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,灾难不打声招呼就冒出来了\N{\rEng}And the whole thing, it just, it-it came out of nowhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.65,0:22:16.29,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我是说 大家早知道有自然环境问题\N{\rEng}I mean, everyone knew there was trouble with the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.31,0:22:19.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,即便是右翼疯子也私下里心知肚明\N{\rEng}I mean, I think even the right-wing nutjobs were secretly, they got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.83,0:22:21.39,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但现在\N{\rEng}But this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.83,0:22:24.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,现在这些\N{\rEng}this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:30.43,Default-3,,0,0,33,,现在这些不过是各种屁事的集合\N{\rEng}this is just 60 different varieties of shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.45,0:22:33.91,Default-3,,0,0,33,,屁事排山倒海地来\N{\rEng}It's just so much shit that happened fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.93,0:22:38.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,现在一年都十四个月了\N{\rEng}It's like a year, man. Fourteen months.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:42.04,Default-3,,0,0,33,,倒霉啊\N{\rEng}Sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.64,0:22:48.52,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊 倒霉啊\N{\rEng}Yeah. Sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.17,0:22:54.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,飞机写字\N{\rEng}Skywriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.61,0:23:00.19,Default-3,,0,0,33,,长大后就再也没见过这种事\N{\rEng}I haven't seen one of those since I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.64,0:22:59.81,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(210,100)\frz-22\fs26\i1\fsp12\blur0.5\1c&HAFB992&}谢谢你 亠亠
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.18,0:23:07.08,Default-3,,0,0,33,,搞什么鬼？\N{\rEng}What the fuck?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.11,0:23:12.57,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我也想问同样的问题\N{\rEng}My sentiments... exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.88,0:23:13.71,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(210,100)\frz-22\fs26\i1\fsp12\blur0.5\1c&HAFB992&}谢谢你 查克
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.29,0:23:23.18,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(20,100,300,100)\fsp2\1c&H22A2C2&\shad1\bord1}谢谢你 查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.83,0:23:25.83,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(20,80,230,80)\fsp2\1c&H5CA179&\shad1\bord1}街头艺人万岁
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.02,0:23:28.06,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(20,80,230,80)\fsp2\1c&H49330F&\2c00FFFFFF\3c00FFFFFF\shad1\bord1}查克万岁
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.13,0:23:29.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(20,80,230,80)\fsp2\1c&H202F75&\2c00222222\3c00222222\shad1\bord1}查克我爱你
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.73,0:23:33.13,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(20,80,230,80)\fsp2\1c&H1196C0&\2c00222222\3c00222222\shad1\bord1}查克yyds
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.01,0:23:41.08,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(100, 100)\fsp2\1c&H0C91BA&\shad1\bord1}爱你 查克
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:47.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,喂 喂 喂  你上哪去了？\N{\rEng}Whoa, whoa, whoa, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.44,0:23:50.73,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你不知道吗？我跑过来的\N{\rEng}Are you kidding? I had to run here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.75,0:23:53.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,路全堵了 一半人把车都仍路上了\N{\rEng}The traffic's insane, and half the cars are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.80,0:23:54.91,Default-3,,0,0,33,,温斯顿医生跑了\N{\rEng}Dr. Winston's MIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.93,0:23:56.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-什么意思？ -你没听错\N{\rEng}-What? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.62,0:23:58.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他今天早上过来看了一圈转头就走了\N{\rEng}He walked in this morning, and he looked around and he walked out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.97,0:24:00.48,Default-3,,0,0,33,,再也找不到他了\N{\rEng}And now I can't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.50,0:24:02.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,他把对讲机都扔门口了\N{\rEng}He dropped his pager when he walked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.46,0:24:04.74,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好 那我来开刀\N{\rEng}Okay. I'll scrub in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.76,0:24:07.09,Default-3,,0,0,33,,床位都空了\N{\rEng}The beds are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.11,0:24:10.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,病人基本都自己走出去了 我把最后一个扶出去的\N{\rEng}Most of them walked out. I-I-I transferred the last of the stable ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.70,0:24:15.09,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但是 菲莉西娅 有点怪事\N{\rEng}But, Felicia, there's something weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:18.57,Default-3,,0,0,33,,怎么回事？\N{\rEng}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.27,0:24:32.46,Default-3,,0,0,33,,机子坏了吗？\N{\rEng}What's wrong with the monitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.49,0:24:36.41,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这就是怪事 不只这一台\N{\rEng}That's the thing, it-it's, it's not just that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.64,0:25:03.11,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我搞不懂 小菲 搞不懂\N{\rEng}I don't know, Fel. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.13,0:25:07.59,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我 我也不想待在这了\N{\rEng}I mean... I might want to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.61,0:25:09.85,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我想回家\N{\rEng}I might wanna go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.87,0:25:14.09,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没必要再待在这了\N{\rEng}I don't think I need to be here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.34,0:25:18.66,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,170)\shad0.5\bord0.5}信号中断
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.87,0:25:41.12,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(154,70)\frz30\fs9\b1\1c&HAFB349&}菲莉西娅
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.44,0:25:44.19,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,108)\frz30\fs9\b1\1c00AAAAAA}呼出失败 无信号
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.06,0:26:38.17,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(180,30,200,60)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.17,0:26:39.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(180,50)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.17,0:26:39.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(190,260)\fs14\i1\frz8\1c&HA1BFB7&\b1}39个{\u1}峥嵘{\u0}岁月！
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.17,0:26:39.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(200,290)\fs14\i1\frz8\1c&HA1BFB7&\b1}谢谢你\N查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.67,0:26:58.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还好吗 老先生？\N{\rEng}You okay, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.72,0:27:02.00,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好 就歇歇脚\N{\rEng}Yeah. Just taking a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.64,0:27:05.88,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我走去市中心看大地坑了\N{\rEng}I walked downtown to look at the sinkhole
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.90,0:27:07.93,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还用手机拍了几张照片\N{\rEng}and take a few pictures with my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.95,0:27:11.28,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我以为电视台可能会想要\N{\rEng}Thought one of the local TV stations might be interested,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.30,0:27:15.54,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但全都停播了\N{\rEng}but they all seem to be off the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.56,0:27:18.67,Default-3,,0,0,33,,除了克兰兹的广告\N{\rEng}Except for pictures of Krantz.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.57,0:27:23.09,Default-3,,0,0,33,,到处都是克兰兹啊\N{\rEng}All Krantz all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:26.29,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-知道他是谁吗？ -不知道\N{\rEng}-Any idea who he is? -None.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.31,0:27:31.65,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我问过至少二十多人 没人知道\N{\rEng}I've asked two dozen people, at least. Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.67,0:27:36.13,Default-3,,0,0,33,,克兰兹可是这个时代的幕后大佬啊\N{\rEng}Our man, Krantz, is the Oz of the apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.15,0:27:38.91,Default-3,,0,0,33,,只闻其名 不见其身啊\N{\rEng}Our last meme.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.93,0:27:41.31,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-你往哪走？ -丰收里\N{\rEng}-Where are you heading? -Harvest Acres.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.33,0:27:44.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,世外桃源般的小区\N{\rEng}Nice little enclave off the beaten track.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.63,0:27:47.04,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我正要去那儿\N{\rEng}I'm heading there myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.06,0:27:48.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-我前妻住那儿 -噢\N{\rEng}-My ex lives there. -Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.55,0:27:49.82,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好吧\N{\rEng}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.90,0:27:52.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要一起去吗？\N{\rEng}I can walk with you if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.27,0:27:54.54,Default-3,,0,0,33,,山姆 你做什么工作的？\N{\rEng}What do you do, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.56,0:27:56.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,如果还有工作的话\N{\rEng}If you still do anything, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.24,0:28:01.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,亚伯勒殡仪馆的老板兼首席殡葬师\N{\rEng}Owner and chief undertaker for Yarborough Funeral Home.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.42,0:28:02.98,Default-3,,0,0,33,,噢 老天\N{\rEng}Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.00,0:28:04.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.26,0:28:06.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,生意之前好到爆\N{\rEng}We had a boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.70,0:28:07.99,Default-3,,0,0,33,,谈起这个就高兴\N{\rEng}It's hard to feel good about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.01,0:28:11.38,Default-3,,0,0,33,,最火的还是前几周\N{\rEng}but business was never better than it was a few weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.14,0:28:17.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但我真正志向所在是气象学\N{\rEng}But my real interest's meteorology.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.80,0:28:21.21,Default-3,,0,0,33,,年轻时我曾想当电视上天气预报员\N{\rEng}Dreamed of being a television weatherman in my salad days,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.21,0:28:23.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许能成全国台的\N{\rEng}maybe even one of the networks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.80,0:28:26.05,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但 没成\N{\rEng}But n-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.07,0:28:27.96,Default-3,,0,0,33,,不过还继续关注着\N{\rEng}I keep up, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.98,0:28:30.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,读有关的书\N{\rEng}Read the journals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.55,0:28:37.10,Default-3,,0,0,33,,想听的话 有些我读到的奇闻异事\N{\rEng}And I can tell you something amazing if you want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.12,0:28:42.11,Default-3,,0,0,33,,大家都说一天有24小时 对吧？\N{\rEng}You know how people say there are 24 hours in a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.13,0:28:44.04,Default-3,,0,0,33,,其实他们错了\N{\rEng}Well, they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.09,0:28:51.55,Default-3,,0,0,33,,在恒星日中一天有23小时零56分钟\N{\rEng}There were 23 hours and 56 minutes in a stellar day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.41,0:29:00.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(250,126)\fs16\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.41,0:29:00.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(260,170)\fs11\i1\frz8\1c&HA4AC88&\b1}39个{\u1}峥嵘{\u0}岁月！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.41,0:29:00.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,156)\fs11\i1\frz8\1c&HA4AC88&\b1}谢谢你\N查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.53,0:28:58.32,Default-3,,0,0,33,,还零几秒钟\N{\rEng}Plus a few odd seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.53,0:29:00.02,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你说的是过去吧？\N{\rEng}There "were"?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.05,0:29:02.16,Default-3,,0,0,33,,根据我的计算\N{\rEng}Based on my calculations,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.19,0:29:05.93,Default-3,,0,0,33,,相信我 我的数学很好\N{\rEng}which I assure you I can back up, my math is good,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.02,0:29:11.40,Default-3,,0,0,33,,现在一天有24小时零2分钟长\N{\rEng}there are now 24 hours and two minutes in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.42,0:29:13.27,Default-3,,0,0,33,,知道这什么意思？\N{\rEng}Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.29,0:29:15.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,地球自转速度在减慢？\N{\rEng}Well, you're saying the Earth's rotation is slowing down?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.46,0:29:17.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没错\N{\rEng}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.08,0:29:22.19,Default-3,,0,0,33,,很多人将这些灾难归咎于我们破坏环境\N{\rEng}Lot of folks think all of these disasters are 'cause of what we've done to the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.21,0:29:23.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,并非如此\N{\rEng}Not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.43,0:29:27.63,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我先承认 我们对待母亲非常坏\N{\rEng}I'm the first to admit, we treated our mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.65,0:29:31.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是的 地球母亲 万物之母\N{\rEng}yes, she's our mother, all of us, very badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.44,0:29:34.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们肯定玷污了她 几近强暴\N{\rEng}Certainly molested her, if not outright raped her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.70,0:29:41.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,但比起宇宙那浩瀚机制 我们只不过是一粒尘埃\N{\rEng}But... we're puny compared to the great clock of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.88,0:29:43.12,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是呀\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.32,0:29:45.00,Default-3,,0,0,33,,不论是什么原因\N{\rEng}Whatever's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.02,0:29:48.87,Default-3,,0,0,33,,问题绝对比环境恶化更大\N{\rEng}is much larger than environmental degradation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.89,0:29:51.57,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这就是数学告诉我的\N{\rEng}The math says so.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.59,0:29:54.53,Default-3,,0,0,33,,数学能做很多事\N{\rEng}And, and math can do a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.55,0:30:01.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,数学可以是门艺术 但数学可不会撒谎\N{\rEng}I mean, math can be art... but it can't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.77,0:30:21.18,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(122, 210)\fs10\fsp2\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c00AAAAAA}丰收里小区
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.82,0:30:10.24,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你看 我要先坐会儿\N{\rEng}You know what? I think I'll sit
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.26,0:30:17.94,Default-3,,0,0,33,,边欣赏日落 边歇歇脚\N{\rEng}and enjoy the sunset while I wait for the arthritis to settle a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.96,0:30:21.25,Default-3,,0,0,33,,要一起坐会儿吗？\N{\rEng}You care to join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.23,0:30:26.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我还想继续走\N{\rEng}I think I'll go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.49,0:30:29.82,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你前妻 我理解\N{\rEng}The ex. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.84,0:30:35.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,好的 一路顺风 安德森先生\N{\rEng}Well, it was nice speaking with you, Mr. Anderson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.37,0:31:16.72,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你好\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.19,0:31:18.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你好\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.07,0:31:24.18,Default-3,,0,0,33,,别怕 我正去我前妻那儿 菲莉西娅·安德森\N{\rEng}Don't worry. I'm going to see my ex-wife, Felicia Anderson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.20,0:31:26.88,Default-3,,0,0,33,,她现在改回娘家姓戈登了\N{\rEng}I think she's back to Gordon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.90,0:31:29.97,Default-3,,0,0,33,,她住在费恩巷19号\N{\rEng}She lives on Fern Lane, number 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.99,0:31:33.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是的 我认识戈登小姐\N{\rEng}Yeah, I know Miss Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.86,0:31:36.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你大晚上出来干嘛？\N{\rEng}What are you doing out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.61,0:31:39.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,溜旱冰\N{\rEng}I wanted to go skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.83,0:31:43.64,Default-3,,0,0,33,,以前我特别喜欢溜旱冰\N{\rEng}I used to love skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.66,0:31:46.79,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那现在就该就去溜\N{\rEng}Then you should go skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.96,0:31:49.51,Default-3,,0,0,33,,也许我真该去溜\N{\rEng}Maybe I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.53,0:31:53.60,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你都跟戈登小姐分手了 咋还去见她？\N{\rEng}Why do you see Miss Gordon if she's your ex?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.62,0:31:55.56,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我还是喜欢她\N{\rEng}I still like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.58,0:31:58.06,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你们吵架吗？\N{\rEng}Do you fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.15,0:31:59.96,Default-3,,0,0,33,,以前吵\N{\rEng}We used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.94,0:32:03.05,Default-3,,0,0,33,,分手后 我们相处得更好了\N{\rEng}We get along better now that we're exes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.07,0:32:06.38,Default-3,,0,0,33,,戈登小姐有时会来送她烤的姜饼干\N{\rEng}Miss Gordon gives us gingersnap cookies sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.41,0:32:08.20,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我其实更喜欢奥利奥 不过...\N{\rEng}I like Oreos better, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.22,0:32:12.07,Default-3,,0,0,33,,就像是盒巧克力 不能每颗都合心意 对吧？\N{\rEng}That's just the way the cookie crumbles, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.07,0:32:13.64,Default-3,,0,0,33,,姜饼干里没巧克力\N{\rEng}Gingersnaps don't crumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.64,0:32:15.85,Default-3,,0,0,33,,除非和奥利奥一起吃...\N{\rEng}At least not until you crunch them...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.22,0:32:27.54,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你抓紧回家吧\N{\rEng}You better go home, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.57,0:32:32.62,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没路灯 天太黑 没法溜\N{\rEng}It's too dark for skating without streetlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.92,0:32:37.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,会没事吗？\N{\rEng}Is everything gonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.89,0:32:41.88,Default-3,,0,0,33,,当然会\N{\rEng}Sure it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.58,0:32:53.13,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(110,110)\frz10\i1\blur0.5\1c&HCCDF97&}谢谢你\N查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.14,0:33:17.92,Default-3,,0,0,33,,回家去\N{\rEng}Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.66,0:33:21.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,回家去找你爸妈\N{\rEng}Go home to your Mom and Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.15,0:33:25.56,Default-3,,0,0,33,,抓紧\N{\rEng}Do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.41,0:34:07.45,Default-3,,0,0,33,,哦 谢天谢地 谢天谢地\N{\rEng}Oh, thank God. Oh, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.84,0:34:11.64,Default-3,,0,0,33,,-谢天谢地 -这些都 都...\N{\rEng}-Thank God. -They, they just...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.24,0:34:16.09,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这些都突然冒出来了\N{\rEng}They just, they just started showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.11,0:34:18.81,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我知道 我知道 我也看到了\N{\rEng}No, I know, I know, I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.90,0:34:20.97,Default-3,,0,0,33,,只是这个小区吗？\N{\rEng}Is it just here?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.99,0:34:23.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我觉得到处都有\N{\rEng}I think it's everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.90,0:34:28.33,Default-3,,0,0,33,,看起来时候到了\N{\rEng}I think it's almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.00,0:34:33.43,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.17,0:34:36.86,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是的 时候到了\N{\rEng}Yeah, I think it's almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.28,0:36:20.78,Default-3,,0,0,33,,这是我见过的最亮的星空\N{\rEng}It's the brightest I've ever seen the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.20,0:36:27.45,Default-3,,0,0,33,,看那里\N{\rEng}Just look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.42,0:36:32.23,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那是天鹰座\N{\rEng}There's Aquila the eagle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.25,0:36:33.68,Default-3,,0,0,33,,嗯\N{\rEng}Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.21,0:36:35.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那是...\N{\rEng}There's, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.86,0:36:38.95,Default-3,,0,0,33,,天鹅座\N{\rEng}Cygnus the swan.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.52,0:36:48.75,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你看到了吗？\N{\rEng}You see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.67,0:37:03.97,Default-3,,0,0,33,,那是北极...\N{\rEng}And there's the North Sta...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.33,0:37:09.70,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你看到刚才那个吗？\N{\rEng}Did you just see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.72,0:37:11.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,看到了\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.42,0:37:18.72,Default-3,,0,0,33,,火星也没了\N{\rEng}There goes Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.53,0:37:36.51,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我好怕\N{\rEng}I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.45,0:37:40.34,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我也是\N{\rEng}I am too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.36,0:37:42.92,Default-3,,0,0,33,,没事的 亲爱的\N{\rEng}It's okay, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.10,0:37:46.88,Default-3,,0,0,33,,你先走一步\N{\rEng}You go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.93,0:37:52.61,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我们到那里再重逢\N{\rEng}You go on ahead, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.90,0:37:59.44,Default-3,,0,0,33,,活了才39年\N{\rEng}Just thirty-nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.35,0:38:09.64,Default-3,,0,0,33,,是39个峥嵘岁月\N{\rEng}Thirty-nine great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.40,0:38:18.15,Default-3,,0,0,33,,谢谢你 查克\N{\rEng}Thanks, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.07,0:38:44.42,Default-3,,0,0,33,,我爱...\N{\rEng}I love y...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.13,0:39:05.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,130)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}第二幕
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.50,0:39:05.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,172)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}街头艺人万岁
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.71,0:39:12.41,Default-2,,0,0,12,,多亏她那开着旧面包车的朋友麦克帮忙\N{\rEng}With the help of her friend, Mac, who has an old van,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.50,0:39:15.82,Default-2,,0,0,12,,泰勒·弗兰克才能把架子鼓摆到\N{\rEng}Taylor Franck sets up her drum kit in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.85,0:39:20.11,Default-2,,0,0,12,,第八街长廊上她最喜欢的那个地方\N{\rEng}her favored spot on the Eighth Street Promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.11,0:39:24.18,Default-2,,0,0,12,,这天是周四下午\N{\rEng}It's Thursday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.20,0:39:27.05,Default-2,,0,0,12,,这天的天气 真是绝了\N{\rEng}The weather is fucking gorgeous,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.08,0:39:31.10,Default-2,,0,0,12,,街上人来人往 大家都在幻想着周末\N{\rEng}and the streets are thronged with people looking forward to the weekend,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.12,0:39:34.06,Default-2,,0,0,12,,毕竟幻想总比现实好\N{\rEng}which is always better than the weekend itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.08,0:39:36.54,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-泰勒 都差不多了吧？ -嗯 谢了\N{\rEng}-All good. Taylor? -Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.56,0:39:39.50,Default-2,,0,0,12,,老铁 别忘分我一成收入\N{\rEng}Ten percent is all the thanks I want, dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.61,0:39:45.95,Default-2,,0,0,12,,泰勒和麦克都在城堡街的心疗唱片店打零工\N{\rEng}Taylor, and Mac too, work part-time at Doctor Records on Castle Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.98,0:39:50.15,Default-2,,0,0,12,,打赏多时 泰勒挣得差不多跟打零工一样\N{\rEng}But on a good day Taylor can make almost as much busking.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.23,0:39:51.34,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(330,176)\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c&H586EAB&\fs20}魔 术 帽\N{\1c&H657D6D&\fs18}每笔打赏都会\N{\1c&H586EAB&\fs18\b1}精彩翻倍!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.32,0:39:57.81,Default-2,,0,0,12,,{\rNote\fs13}茱莉亚学院是世界顶尖的音乐学校{\r}\N当初考上{\u1}茱莉亚{\u0}时 她爸妈可没料到她会上街打鼓\N{\rEng}Busk-drumming isn't what her parents saw for her when she enrolled at {\u1}Juilliard{\u0},
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.89,0:40:01.02,Default-2,,0,0,12,,更不知道她现在还辍了学\N{\rEng}and they don't know yet that she dropped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.46,0:40:04.68,Default-2,,0,0,12,,在茱莉亚他们教你多动脑子\N{\rEng}Juilliard wanted you to think about what you were doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.77,0:40:14.94,Default-2,,0,0,12,,在泰勒眼里 跟着鼓点走就对了 多想一下灵感就跑了\N{\rEng}but as far as Taylor is concerned, the beat is your friend and thinking is the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.69,0:40:21.41,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她先热身 一开始节奏简单\N{\rEng}She starts warming up, going easy at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.43,0:40:24.20,Default-2,,0,0,12,,节奏缓慢 不敲牛铃\N{\rEng}slow tempo, no cowbell,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.40,0:40:29.60,Default-2,,0,0,12,,不在乎魔术帽空着 里面只有她自己放的钱\N{\rEng}not minding that the magic hat stays empty except for her two crumpled dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.62,0:40:35.39,Default-2,,0,0,12,,还有个滑板小子随随便便丢进去的硬币\N{\rEng}and a quarter flipped contemptuously by a dude on a skateboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.41,0:40:39.21,Default-2,,0,0,12,,时间还早 总能找到切入点\N{\rEng}There is time. There is a way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.23,0:40:45.52,Default-2,,0,0,12,,找到切入点才是占最大头的乐趣\N{\rEng}Finding the in is half the fun. Maybe even most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.37,0:40:52.27,Default-2,,0,0,12,,珍妮丝·哈利迪在书店工作一天后正在回家\N{\rEng}Janice Halliday is on her way home from seven hours at Paper and Page,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.29,0:40:55.45,Default-2,,0,0,12,,大概会去海边走走\N{\rEng}and may walk all the way to the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.47,0:40:59.10,Default-2,,0,0,12,,谈了一年多的男友刚甩了她\N{\rEng}Her boyfriend of 16 months just broke up with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.12,0:41:01.57,Default-2,,0,0,12,,随便发个消息甩了她\N{\rEng}and he did it the modern way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.17,0:41:01.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,108)\frz-12\fs9\1c00444444\b1}女：怎么不回我消息了？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.17,0:41:01.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,150)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：咱俩不合适
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.17,0:41:01.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,174)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：你是个好人
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.17,0:41:01.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(256,184)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：继续做朋友？？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.57,0:41:02.98,Default-2,,0,0,12,,王八蛋！\N{\rEng}Motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.00,0:41:10.03,Default-2,,0,0,12,,这突如其来 犹如当头一棒把门关在脸上\N{\rEng}It was totally unexpected, like having a door slammed in your face just as you were getting ready to walk through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.05,0:41:11.59,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-那感觉... -真他妈离谱\N{\rEng}-It was... -Fucking bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.61,0:41:13.16,Default-2,,0,0,12,,...真他妈离谱\N{\rEng}...fucking bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.18,0:41:17.43,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她从没动过真情 也没天真地以为自己爱过他\N{\rEng}She isn't in love with him. never even kidded herself that she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.45,0:41:19.30,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-但依然... -他喵的糟透了\N{\rEng}-But still it... -Fucking sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.32,0:41:22.61,Default-2,,0,0,12,,...打她个措手不及\N{\rEng}...is a dismaying shock just the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.63,0:41:27.65,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她打算回家后喝点酒 顺便哭一场\N{\rEng}She supposes she'll have some wine when she gets home and cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.67,0:41:33.09,Default-2,,0,0,12,,说不定还会播个爵士乐 在屋里醉舞一番\N{\rEng}Maybe queue up one of her big band playlists and dance drunk around the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.11,0:41:35.88,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她读高中时就爱跳舞\N{\rEng}She loved to dance in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.90,0:41:38.80,Default-2,,0,0,12,,也许能借此重温当年那份快乐\N{\rEng}Maybe she can recapture a little of that happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.82,0:41:41.03,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-去你妈的 -你说什么？\N{\rEng}-Fucking really?! -Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.05,0:41:43.52,Default-2,,0,0,12,,对不起 对不起 没说你 没说你\N{\rEng}Sorry, sorry, sorry. Not you, not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.34,0:41:45.96,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他喵的！\N{\rEng}Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.04,0:41:48.52,Default-2,,0,0,12,,查克的拿铁好了\N{\rEng}Got an oat milk latte for Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.46,0:41:49.65,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,130)\frz14\1c00222222\b1}查 克  {\fs20}^{\fs12}v{\fs20}^
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.48,0:41:51.32,Default-2,,0,0,12,,查尔斯·查克·克兰兹\N{\rEng}Charles Krantz,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.79,0:41:56.33,Default-2,,0,0,12,,在朋友眼中 他总一身会计行头\N{\rEng}Chuck to his friends, is dressed in the armor of accountancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.35,0:41:59.95,Default-2,,0,0,12,,灰西装 蓝衬衣配蓝领带\N{\rEng}Gray suit, blue shirt, blue tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.97,0:42:04.95,Default-2,,0,0,12,,脚上那双温莎牌皮鞋虽不贵 却耐穿\N{\rEng}His Samuel Windsor shoes are inexpensive but sturdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.97,0:42:11.22,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他来这参加个主题为“二十一世纪银行业”的研讨会\N{\rEng}He's here for a week-long conference titled "Banking in the 21st Century."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.24,0:42:14.96,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他的中西部信托银行派他来的\N{\rEng}He's been sent by his bank, Midwest Trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.98,0:42:16.88,Default-2,,0,0,12,,全程报销\N{\rEng}all expenses paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.90,0:42:20.75,Default-2,,0,0,12,,查克对嘉宾和座谈都挺有兴趣\N{\rEng}Chuck has enjoyed the speakers and the panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.77,0:42:22.32,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他上过一个座谈会\N{\rEng}He was on one panel
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.34,0:42:27.37,Default-2,,0,0,12,,明天中午大会结束前还要再参加一个\N{\rEng}and is scheduled to be on another before the conference ends at noon tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.39,0:42:33.76,Default-2,,0,0,12,,但他可不想下班后还和那群同行混在一起\N{\rEng}but has no wish to spend his off-duty hours in the company of 70 other accountants.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.78,0:42:39.12,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他精通会计的那套行话 也觉得自己能融入别的圈子\N{\rEng}He speaks their language, but likes to think he speaks others as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.14,0:42:44.94,Default-2,,0,0,12,,至少曾经那么自信 如今却大不如前了\N{\rEng}At least he did, although some of the vocabulary is now lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.96,0:42:51.00,Default-2,,0,0,12,,现在 他穿着他温莎牌牛津鞋正在午后散步\N{\rEng}Now, his sensible Samuel Windsor Oxfords are taking him for an afternoon walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.02,0:42:55.05,Default-2,,0,0,12,,现在的生活没能达到最初的设想\N{\rEng}His life is narrower than the one he once hoped for,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.07,0:42:57.41,Default-2,,0,0,12,,可他已经释然了\N{\rEng}but he's made peace with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.46,0:43:02.79,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他明白水往低处流是自然规律\N{\rEng}He understands that narrowing is the natural order of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.81,0:43:07.41,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他有个忠贞不渝的妻子叫珍妮\N{\rEng}He has a wife, Ginny, to whom he is scrupulously faithful,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.43,0:43:11.54,Default-2,,0,0,12,,还有个聪明风趣的儿子上初中\N{\rEng}and an intelligent, good-humored son in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.56,0:43:18.19,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他还有九个月可活 只不过他还不知道\N{\rEng}He also has only nine months to live, though he doesn't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.61,0:43:28.94,Default-2,,0,0,12,,泰勒已经敲了十分钟了 分文未得 毫无灵感\N{\rEng}Taylor has been on the job for 10 minutes now and has nothing to show for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.97,0:43:33.91,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她看见个西装男朝她走来\N{\rEng}She sees a Mr. Businessman type coming toward her
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.93,0:43:36.43,Default-2,,0,0,12,,不知为何 他身上有股气息\N{\rEng}and something about him, God knows what,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.45,0:43:41.52,Default-2,,0,0,12,,让泰勒忍不住大张旗鼓宣布他登场了\N{\rEng}makes Taylor want to announce his approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.54,0:43:46.06,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她先用松弛的摇摆热场 又切换到更撩人的节奏\N{\rEng}She slips first into a reggae beat, then something slinkier.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.08,0:43:50.40,Default-2,,0,0,12,,今天头一次 泰勒火花被点燃\N{\rEng}And for the first time today, Taylor feels a spark
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.42,0:43:54.67,Default-2,,0,0,12,,便在核心鼓点上敲着牛铃\N{\rEng}and begins to whack the cowbell on the downbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.69,0:43:56.10,Default-2,,0,0,12,,真带感\N{\rEng}It's pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.12,0:44:02.92,Default-2,,0,0,12,,鼓点已经到来 那律动带你一路向前\N{\rEng}The groove has arrived, and the groove is like a road you want to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.92,0:44:06.68,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她本可把节拍提快 玩点花样\N{\rEng}She could speed the beat up, get some tom in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.70,0:44:12.17,Default-2,,0,0,12,,但此刻目光是那西装男 多此一举反而不搭\N{\rEng}but she's watching Mr. Businessman and that seems wrong for this dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.19,0:44:18.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,她以为那西装男只是路过 要去商务酒店\N{\rEng}She believes Mr. Businessman will just go on past on his way to the business hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.71,0:44:23.87,Default-2,,0,0,12,,等他一走 泰勒再换节拍\N{\rEng}and when he's gone, Taylor will switch to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.89,0:44:28.03,Default-2,,0,0,12,,可他却停下脚步\N{\rEng}But instead of floating on by...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.95,0:46:47.10,Default-2,,0,0,12,,赏个脸\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.47,0:46:50.02,Default-2,,0,0,12,,来吧 小老妹\N{\rEng}Come on, little sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.61,0:46:51.72,Default-2,,0,0,12,,来跳舞吧\N{\rEng}Let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.74,0:46:53.26,Default-2,,0,0,12,,跳\N{\rEng}Dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.61,0:46:58.44,Default-2,,0,0,12,,对了\N{\rEng}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.53,0:47:01.06,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我带你跳 有我别怕\N{\rEng}I'll lead you. I got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.49,0:47:50.88,Default-2,,0,0,12,,啊\N{\rEng}Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.63,0:47:59.25,Default-2,,0,0,12,,没事 眼镜的事儿 眼镜的事儿\N{\rEng}It's okay. It's my glasses. It's my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.86,0:49:40.99,Default-2,,0,0,12,,现在该做什么？\N{\rEng}What are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.78,0:49:42.82,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我也不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.71,0:50:01.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,大伙 今天就到这了\N{\rEng}No more today, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.88,0:50:03.48,Default-2,,0,0,12,,今天就到这了\N{\rEng}No more today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.84,0:50:07.25,Default-2,,0,0,12,,今天就到这了 得见好就收\N{\rEng}No more today. We gotta quit while we're ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.91,0:50:11.82,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(330,146)\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c&H586EAB&\fs20}魔 术 帽\N{\1c&H657D6D&\fs18}每笔打赏都会\N{\1c&H586EAB&\fs18\b1}精彩翻倍!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.54,0:50:11.29,Default-2,,0,0,12,,要搭把手吗\N{\rEng}Do you need a-any help at all or...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.37,0:50:12.81,Default-2,,0,0,12,,好 帮把这个收起来\N{\rEng}Here, can you, uh, take this?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.89,0:50:14.42,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-好 -拧这里\N{\rEng}-Sure. -Just, just spin the thingy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.50,0:50:16.47,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-小心别夹手了 -会雨过天晴的\N{\rEng}But watch out for your fingers. -It'll, it'll, it'll get 'em good.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.55,0:50:18.30,Default-2,,0,0,12,,懂了吧\N{\rEng}you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.37,0:50:20.50,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-好 好 -找点事散散心\N{\rEng}-Yeah, yeah. -To doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.60,0:50:22.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,刚太神奇了\N{\rEng}What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.77,0:50:24.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,跳的太神了\N{\rEng}That was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.78,0:50:26.13,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你们是舞蹈演员吗？\N{\rEng}You dance for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.21,0:50:27.87,Default-2,,0,0,12,,哦 不 不\N{\rEng}No. Oh, no. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.95,0:50:29.87,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-不 不是的 -你做什么的？\N{\rEng}-No, I do not, sir. -What do you do for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.96,0:50:31.85,Default-2,,0,0,12,,哎呦 我好像不小心搞坏了\N{\rEng}Oh, no, I think I... Did I... I didn't break it, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.87,0:50:34.07,Default-2,,0,0,12,,这个好像坏了\N{\rEng}I think he broke it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.31,0:50:36.84,Default-2,,0,0,12,,去喷泉吧\N{\rEng}Let's hit the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.92,0:50:39.17,Default-2,,0,0,12,,那儿没停车位\N{\rEng}We'll never find parking by the Common.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.53,0:50:40.57,Default-2,,0,0,12,,那也要停\N{\rEng}We will today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.92,0:50:46.19,Default-2,,0,0,12,,今天 就像魔术一样\N{\rEng}Today...is magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.67,0:50:54.47,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你们在哪练的这身舞功？\N{\rEng}Where did you learn to dance like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.16,0:51:02.40,Default-2,,0,0,12,,别 别 别 那是你赚的\N{\rEng}Oh, no, no, no, that's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.42,0:51:04.01,Default-2,,0,0,12,,不 有福同享\N{\rEng}Nope, we split it even.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.03,0:51:08.47,Default-2,,0,0,12,,要我自己敲 一天也赚不了这么多\N{\rEng}By myself, I wouldn't have made half as much if I drummed till midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:18.61,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你没事吧？\N{\rEng}You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.66,0:51:22.34,Default-2,,0,0,12,,还好\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.92,0:51:26.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,就是有点头疼\N{\rEng}Yeah. Just one of my headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.36,0:51:30.82,Default-2,,0,0,12,,不了 不了 真用不着 你留着吧\N{\rEng}Oh, no, no, no. Come on. I don't need it. You keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.84,0:51:33.26,Default-2,,0,0,12,,来吧 老兄 你应得的\N{\rEng}Come on, man, you earned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.28,0:51:40.00,Default-2,,0,0,12,,拿去吃顿饭 转手送人也行 但这钱我偏要交给你\N{\rEng}Buy yourself dinner. Give it away. But I'm handing it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.64,0:51:44.40,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你们干这行都能当职业了\N{\rEng}You could do this for a living, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.42,0:51:46.36,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我可不敢这么说\N{\rEng}I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.38,0:51:50.30,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我真觉得靠街头表演 我们能红 能赚大钱\N{\rEng}I really think we could busk our way to fame and fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.78,0:51:56.83,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你怎么会停在我面前？\N{\rEng}What made you stop in front of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.04,0:52:01.62,Default-2,,0,0,12,,又为什么突然跳起舞？\N{\rEng}Why did you start moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.90,0:52:08.47,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他本可以说 鼓点让他想起了他那不成气候的追旧青年乐队\N{\rEng}He could say it was because he was thinking about his old half-assed band, The Retros,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.49,0:52:14.37,Default-2,,0,0,12,,还有他多么的喜欢跟着节奏跳舞\N{\rEng}and how he liked to dance across the stage during instrumental breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.41,0:52:16.16,Default-2,,0,0,12,,但他没这么说\N{\rEng}But that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.59,0:52:21.76,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我也说不清\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.50,0:52:25.96,Default-2,,0,0,12,,泰勒 该走了\N{\rEng}Taylor, we gotta roll,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.98,0:52:29.45,Default-2,,0,0,12,,不然你赚的钱都得交罚单了\N{\rEng}or you're gonna end up spending your take on my parking ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.99,0:52:33.06,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你们不考虑转行跳舞吗？\N{\rEng}So, you guys don't want a career change?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.08,0:52:34.97,Default-2,,0,0,12,,转行？\N{\rEng}Career change? How... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.99,0:52:37.28,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我们肯定能闯出名堂\N{\rEng}We'll make a name for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.39,0:52:40.98,Default-2,,0,0,12,,别急着走 先进来一下\N{\rEng}You got to get in here before you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.00,0:52:43.07,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-来个大团抱！ -哦 哦 好\N{\rEng}-Group hug. -Oh, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.09,0:52:44.40,Default-2,,0,0,12,,-大团抱！ -来\N{\rEng}-Group hug. -Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.48,0:52:45.98,Default-2,,0,0,12,,快 快 快\N{\rEng}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.00,0:52:47.60,Default-2,,0,0,12,,来 来\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.88,0:52:55.86,Default-2,,0,0,12,,街头艺人万岁\N{\rEng}Buskers forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.88,0:52:57.43,Default-2,,0,0,12,,好了 好了\N{\rEng}Yeah. Buskers forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.45,0:53:00.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,得赶在贴罚单前抓紧走\N{\rEng}We gotta roll before the meter maid shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.94,0:53:07.61,Default-2,,0,0,12,,真替你难过\N{\rEng}I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.07,0:53:09.31,Default-2,,0,0,12,,真倒霉\N{\rEng}That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.33,0:53:11.29,Default-2,,0,0,12,,这确实倒霉\N{\rEng}It does suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.94,0:53:13.88,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我真觉得他人还不错\N{\rEng}I thought he was a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.90,0:53:17.42,Default-2,,0,0,12,,床上功夫也到位 我们在一起挺开心的\N{\rEng}He was a pretty good lover, and we had fun and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.69,0:53:22.37,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我回去得找下我们跳舞的视频 估计会上热搜\N{\rEng}If I can find a video of us dancing, which I'm gonna look because I bet we go viral,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.39,0:53:29.94,Default-2,,0,0,12,,然后转发给他 再附句“这就是你错过的缘分”\N{\rEng}I'm gonna send it to him with a text, a text that says, "This is what you're missing."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.58,0:53:38.68,Default-2,,0,0,12,,你会没事的\N{\rEng}You're gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.06,0:53:43.71,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我不是全都懂 可这件事我很清楚\N{\rEng}I don't know a lot, but I know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.41,0:53:52.64,Default-2,,0,0,12,,光辉就在你前面 往前迈一步乌云就消散\N{\rEng}You got a bright sunbeam in front of you, and you're gonna step right into it, I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.07,0:53:54.24,Default-2,,0,0,12,,但现在\N{\rEng}But yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.38,0:53:59.35,Default-2,,0,0,12,,真倒霉 没啥好说的\N{\rEng}It sucks. Not much else to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.64,0:54:06.02,Default-2,,0,0,12,,一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉\N{\rEng}Everything goes down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.05,0:54:07.22,Default-2,,0,0,12,,对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.04,0:54:11.94,Default-2,,0,0,12,,说不定谁都躲不掉这劫\N{\rEng}Maybe we're going down the drain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.96,0:54:13.64,Default-2,,0,0,12,,说不定\N{\rEng}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.66,0:54:17.42,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我走这条路\N{\rEng}I'm this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.58,0:54:22.39,Default-2,,0,0,12,,我往那边走\N{\rEng}Uh, I'm that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.24,0:54:29.62,Default-2,,0,0,12,,多谢你陪我跳舞\N{\rEng}Thank you for the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.03,0:55:27.36,Default-2,,0,0,12,,当他走过泰勒摆鼓的地方\N{\rEng}As he passes the place where Taylor set up her drums,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.38,0:55:31.43,Default-2,,0,0,12,,那两个问题又冒了出来\N{\rEng}those two questions recur.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.30,0:55:36.28,Default-2,,0,0,12,,为什么要停下脚步听？\N{\rEng}Why did he stop to listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.30,0:55:41.27,Default-2,,0,0,12,,又为什么要跳起舞？\N{\rEng}And why did he start to dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.05,0:55:45.13,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他自己也想不通\N{\rEng}He doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.31,0:55:51.21,Default-2,,0,0,12,,有答案能让这回忆更动人吗？\N{\rEng}And would answers make a good thing better?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.23,0:55:54.91,Default-2,,0,0,12,,后来 他走路都成问题\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose the ability to walk,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.93,0:55:59.74,Default-2,,0,0,12,,和那个小老妹跳舞成了个传说\N{\rEng}never mind dancing with little sister on the promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.76,0:56:04.14,Default-2,,0,0,12,,再后来 他咀嚼都成了难题\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose the ability to chew food.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.16,0:56:08.19,Default-2,,0,0,12,,再后来 他记不住妻子的名字\N{\rEng}Later, he'll forget his wife's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.21,0:56:14.15,Default-2,,0,0,12,,到最后 他分不清白日黑夜\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose his grip on the difference between waking and sleeping
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.17,0:56:23.16,Default-2,,0,0,12,,陷入一种让人质疑生命意义的巨大痛苦中\N{\rEng}and enter a land of pain so great he will wonder why God made the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.18,0:56:30.08,Default-2,,0,0,12,,但有时 他还会记得当初把公文包一丢\N{\rEng}What he will remember, occasionally, is how he stopped and dropped his briefcase
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.10,0:56:34.69,Default-2,,0,0,12,,跟着鼓点起舞的感觉\N{\rEng}and began to move his hips to the beat of the drums.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.71,0:56:40.83,Default-2,,0,0,12,,他会觉得 这就是上帝让世界存在的意义\N{\rEng}And he will think that is why God made the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.85,0:56:42.93,Default-2,,0,0,12,,仅此而已\N{\rEng}Just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.08,0:57:04.16,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,130)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}第一幕
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.39,0:57:04.16,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,172)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}我包罗万象
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.05,0:57:09.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克一直盼着能有个小妹妹\N{\rEng}Chuck was looking forward to having a baby sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.96,0:57:13.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,更盼着父母能赶紧回来\N{\rEng}Of course, he was also looking forward to having parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.97,0:57:22.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谁料95号高架上结的冰让一切化为泡影\N{\rEng}but none of that worked out thanks to a patch 95 of well-hidden ice on an I-95 overpass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.59,0:57:26.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事发时查克没在车上\N{\rEng}Chuck wasn't in the car when it happened
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.15,0:57:28.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他父母去享受二人世界\N{\rEng}because his parents were having a dinner date
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.94,0:57:32.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那天晚上他爷爷奶奶带他\N{\rEng}and he was being babysat by his grandparents,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.38,0:57:36.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\rNote\fs13}Zaydee和Bubbie是东欧犹太移民常用的祖父母称呼{\r}\N他那会儿还叫他们{\u1}阿爷阿奶{\u0}\N{\rEng}who, at the time, he was still calling {\u1}Zaydee{\u0} and {\u1}Bubbie{\u0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.29,0:57:37.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他那时七岁了\N{\rEng}He was seven years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.86,0:57:39.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真赞喔\N{\rEng}Excellent job.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.21,0:57:46.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一年半载 屋子里全是悲伤\N{\rEng}For a year and a half, it was a house of unadulterated sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.09,0:57:50.99,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对阿尔比和莎拉·克兰兹来说 不只是儿子和儿媳没了\N{\rEng}Albie and Sarah Krantz had not only lost their son and daughter-in-law...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.01,0:57:52.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,咋不吃饭了？\N{\rEng}Why're you not eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.49,0:57:57.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那本该三个月后出生的孙女也没了\N{\rEng}...they had lost the granddaughter who would've been born just three months later.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.09,0:57:58.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,咋回事儿？\N{\rEng}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.79,0:58:01.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,名字都选好了...\N{\rEng}The name had already been picked out...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.10,0:58:03.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-她叫艾雨莎 -艾雨莎\N{\rEng}-Her name is Alyssa. -...Alyssa.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.54,0:58:07.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克说那名字听着像下雨时\N{\rEng}When Chuck said that sounded to him like rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.06,0:58:11.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他妈哭笑不得\N{\rEng}his mother had laughed and cried at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.15,0:58:14.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他永远忘不了那表情\N{\rEng}He never forgot that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.85,0:58:19.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比靠两件事来排解悲伤\N{\rEng}Albie processed his grief by turning to his two absolutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.82,0:58:23.19,Default-1,,0,0,0,,算账和喝酒\N{\rEng}numbers and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.21,0:58:28.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但对莎拉来说 一切却都失去了滋味\N{\rEng}Sarah, though, could find no joy in her usual pleasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.13,0:58:32.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,曾让她陶醉的音乐 艺术和美食\N{\rEng}She loved the flavors of life, music, art, and food,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.00,0:58:38.50,Default-1,,0,0,0,,如今都索然无味\N{\rEng}but now, found the world quiet and gray and flavorless.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.36,0:58:44.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,随着时间流逝 家里又慢慢有了些温暖\N{\rEng}Some of the good feelings came back into the house with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.88,0:58:48.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事故后全靠外卖度日\N{\rEng}There were a lot of takeout meals after the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.50,0:58:53.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但查克快十岁那年 他奶奶又重新下厨\N{\rEng}but around the time Chuck turned 10, his grandma started cooking again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.76,0:58:57.59,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她做饭时爱放摇滚乐\N{\rEng}She liked rock-and-roll while she was cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.61,0:59:05.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克肯定觉得太潮了 可她显然乐在其中\N{\rEng}Music Chuck would've thought much too young for her, but which she clearly enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.23,0:59:27.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来吧 小老弟 来跳舞吧\N{\rEng}Come on, little brother, let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.58,0:59:58.79,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《西区故事》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.24,1:00:02.11,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《雨中曲》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.60,1:00:04.73,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《歌厅》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.84,1:00:08.98,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《爵士春秋》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.39,1:00:15.23,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《封面女郎》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.21,1:00:22.51,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(340,16)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}电影《封面女郎》(1944)
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.54,1:00:27.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小宝 你有本事学会 你天生是跳舞的料\N{\rEng}You could learn those moves, kiddo. You're a natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.40,1:00:28.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你在哪学的？\N{\rEng}Wh-Where did you learn?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.81,1:00:30.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,高中\N{\rEng}High school.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.07,1:00:34.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你上高中的时候是什么样的？\N{\rEng}What were you like in high school?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.34,1:00:36.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\rNote\fs13}Kusit为希伯来语{\r}\N我可是个{\u1}小辣妹{\u0}\N{\rEng}I was a {\u1}kusit{\u0}.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.69,1:00:39.21,Default-1,,0,0,0,,千万别把我这话告诉你阿爷哦\N{\rEng}But don't you tell your Zaydee I said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.24,1:00:42.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他是个老古董\N{\rEng}He's old school, that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.57,1:00:46.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克守口如瓶\N{\rEng}Chuck never told.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.58,1:00:50.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他把爷爷奶奶家处处都当自己家\N{\rEng}His grandparents' house became every inch his home
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.89,1:00:56.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,除了塔尖阁楼\N{\rEng}with one exception. the cupola on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.89,1:01:01.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克被严令禁止进那阁楼\N{\rEng}Chuck was forbidden to go into the cupola.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.93,1:01:08.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那是他爷爷的一条铁律 不容置疑\N{\rEng}That was his grandfather's rule, and it was absolute, emphatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.38,1:01:11.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他爷爷阿尔比做事宽容\N{\rEng}Albie wasn't a stern man in other matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.77,1:01:15.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,平时人挺温和的\N{\rEng}He was downright gentle in most respects.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.08,1:01:19.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,偏偏在这事上绝不讲情面\N{\rEng}But on this point, he was rigid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.29,1:01:24.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克可不止问过一次\N{\rEng}Chuck asked about it, of course, and more than once.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.26,1:01:28.24,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那上头有什么？从高高的窗户能看到啥？\N{\rEng}What was up there? What could you see from the high window?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.26,1:01:33.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最重要的是 为啥老是锁着？\N{\rEng}And the big question, why was the room locked?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.49,1:01:34.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他奶奶说...\N{\rEng}Grandma said...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.37,1:01:36.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,楼上地板不结实 一踩就会坍下去\N{\rEng}Because the floor isn't safe and you might go right through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.91,1:01:37.82,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他爷爷说...\N{\rEng}Grandpa said...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.82,1:01:41.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,由于那烂地板 屋子里空无一物\N{\rEng}There's nothing up there because of that rotten floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.08,1:01:44.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你往窗外瞅 也就只能看到商场\N{\rEng}And the only thing you can see through the windows is the shopping center.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.98,1:01:50.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他一直这么说 直到查克十一岁生日前一晚\N{\rEng}He said that until, one night, just before Chuck's 11th birthday,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.42,1:01:53.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他才吐出部分实情\N{\rEng}when he told at least part of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.10,1:01:54.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}宇宙历年法\N{\rEng}{\i1}The cosmic calendar
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.81,1:01:59.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}把宇宙的历史压缩到一本365天日历\N{\rEng}{\i1}compresses the local history of the universe into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.56,1:02:02.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}从1月1日宇宙诞生算起\N{\rEng}{\i1}If the universe began on January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.12,1:02:04.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我们的银河系要到5月才出现\N{\rEng}{\i1}it was not until May that the Milky Way formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.87,1:02:07.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,俗话说酒后吐真言\N{\rEng}Drinking is not good for secrets.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.74,1:02:13.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当儿子 儿媳还有那个名字听着像下雨的\N{\rEng}And after the death of his son, daughter-in-law, and granddaughter-to-be,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.18,1:02:15.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,未来孙女艾雨莎全都去世后\N{\rEng}Alyssa, who sounds like rain,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.90,1:02:18.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比·克兰兹就拼命喝酒\N{\rEng}Albie Krantz drank a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.73,1:02:22.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}人类全部的历史 都在\N{\rEng}{\i1}Everything humans have ever done occurred in that bright speck
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.45,1:02:26.00,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}这本日历的最后一天\N{\rEng}{\i1}at the lower right of the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.00,1:02:31.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我打赌 从阁楼往外看 能看到西福商场\N{\rEng}I'll bet you could see way past the Westford Mall from the cupola.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.98,1:02:37.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,整座小镇肯定也能看得一清二楚\N{\rEng}You gotta be able to see the whole town from up there, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.38,1:02:43.71,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要真上去了 你看见的可不只是风景\N{\rEng}If you went up there, you might see a lot more than you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.73,1:02:46.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小查 这门紧锁是有原因的\N{\rEng}That's why it's locked, Chucko.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.20,1:02:49.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}日历里每个月代表12.5亿年\N{\rEng}{\i1}Every month is one and a quarter billion years long.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.39,1:02:52.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}每一天代表4000万年\N{\rEng}{\i1}Each day represents 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.20,1:02:55.21,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他想问清楚\N{\rEng}He wanted to ask what Grandpa meant.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.35,1:02:59.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,尽管他才10岁\N{\rEng}But the adult part of him, not there in person, no, not at 10,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.18,1:03:04.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可脑子里的成熟声音冒出来\N{\rEng}but something that had begun to speak on rare occasions,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.09,1:03:11.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,告诉他别吭声 安静地等着\N{\rEng}told him to be quiet. Be quiet and wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.16,1:03:16.22,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}人类的全部历史就像我手掌那么大\N{\rEng}{\i1}But all of human history would occupy an area the size of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.24,1:03:21.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}现在让我们回到太古时代...\N{\rEng}{\i1}We're just beginning to trace the long and tortuous path which began with the primeval...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.38,1:03:24.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你知道这房子是什么风格的吗？\N{\rEng}You know what style of house this is?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.51,1:03:26.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,维多利亚风格\N{\rEng}Victorian.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.03,1:03:27.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.34,1:03:34.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可不是仿古的 1885年建的正经维多利亚式\N{\rEng}And not pretend Victorian either. It was built in 1885.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.39,1:03:37.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,后来翻新过大概六次吧\N{\rEng}It's been remodeled half a dozen times since.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.44,1:03:42.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可那阁楼一直保留至今\N{\rEng}But that cupola was there from the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.36,1:03:44.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我七十年代初搬来\N{\rEng}Been here since '71.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.88,1:03:50.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,搬来至今 我上那阁楼都没到六次\N{\rEng}And in all those years, I haven't been up to that damn cupola half a dozen times.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.33,1:03:52.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,因为地板烂了？\N{\rEng}'Cause the floor is rotted?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.76,1:03:56.82,Default-1,,0,0,0,,因为闹鬼\N{\rEng}'Cause it's full of ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.24,1:04:00.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}...发生在12月31日的晚上10点30分\N{\rEng}{\i1}...around 10:30 p.m. on December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.94,1:04:03.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-还记得圣诞述异那个故事吗？ -嗯\N{\rEng}-Y-You remember Scrooge? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.29,1:04:04.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那部叫做《圣诞欢歌》的电影？\N{\rEng}That Scrooge movie we watched?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.97,1:04:06.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,记得\N{\rEng}I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.29,1:04:09.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你觉得那算鬼故事吗？\N{\rEng}Do you think of that as a ghost story?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.95,1:04:11.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,应该算吧\N{\rEng}I-I-I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.65,1:04:15.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有人说那是鬼故事\N{\rEng}Heard someone say it was a ghost story.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.87,1:04:19.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他吓的说“圣诞节未卜先知”\N{\rEng}Christmas Yet to Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.74,1:04:24.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}晚上11点59分20秒...\N{\rEng}{\i1}11:59:20, evening, last day of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.70,1:04:28.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,杰弗里家那男孩一个月后就没了\N{\rEng}Jefferies boy was a month later.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.88,1:04:39.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亨利·彼得森拖得久些 等了四五年\N{\rEng}Henry Peterson, that took longer. Four...maybe five years on.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.76,1:04:47.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到那时 阁楼里看到的 我几乎忘得精光\N{\rEng}And by then...I almost forgot what I saw up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.55,1:04:50.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几乎\N{\rEng}Almost.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.93,1:04:56.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我说过再也不上去\N{\rEng}Said I'd never go back up there after that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.65,1:05:03.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真不想上去 要不是为了莎拉\N{\rEng}And I wish I hadn't because of Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.52,1:05:08.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,为了你的阿奶 小查\N{\rEng}Because of your Bubbie, Chucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.53,1:05:12.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最疼你的阿奶\N{\rEng}Your sweet Bubbie.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.45,1:05:15.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,都是面包\N{\rEng}And the bread.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.36,1:05:19.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我们听说过的所有人...\N{\rEng}{\i1}Every person we've ever heard of, somewhere in there...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.02,1:05:23.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这就是等待 小查\N{\rEng}It's the waiting, Chucko.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.11,1:05:26.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这是最难熬的\N{\rEng}That's the hard part.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.20,1:05:28.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}所有历史书上的事 都只...\N{\rEng}{\i1}Everything in the history books happended...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.00,1:05:34.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}发生在这本日历最后10秒钟里\N{\rEng}{\i1}here in the last 10 seconds of the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.18,1:05:37.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,呜 外面真冷\N{\rEng}Ooh! It's getting cold out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.53,1:05:41.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,维拉向大家问好 还谢我煲的汤\N{\rEng}Vera says hi. She says thanks for the soup.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.18,1:05:44.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她把八卦全抖给我 抖得可带劲了\N{\rEng}She laid the gossip on me, laid it good.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.30,1:05:47.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当然 要不然咱咋离不开她呢\N{\rEng}Of course...That's why we have a Vera, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.37,1:05:49.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有什么新鲜事吗？\N{\rEng}So, what's the latest?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.40,1:05:54.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不知道你听说了没 凯伦和马蒂在搞婚姻咨询\N{\rEng}Well, I don't know if you've heard, but Trish is saying Karen and Matty are in therapy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.75,1:05:57.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-搞什么？ -阿爷 亨利·彼得森到底是谁？\N{\rEng}-Again. -Who's Henry Peterson, Zaydee?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.67,1:06:03.00,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}...珍惜我们的宇宙 不要辜负这150亿年\N{\rEng}{\i1}...the universe that made us or we can squander our 15 billion-year heritage.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.02,1:06:05.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再买点煎饼粉\N{\rEng}And get some pancake mix.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.11,1:06:07.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要黄盒的 别买橙盒的 都记住了吗？\N{\rEng}Yellow box, not the orange box. You got all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.80,1:06:09.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,记住了\N{\rEng}I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.20,1:06:11.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-要我写下来吗？ -我记得住\N{\rEng}-Do you need me to write it down? -I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.98,1:06:15.30,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别开车 走路去能醒醒酒\N{\rEng}Don't you think about driving. The walk will sober you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.33,1:06:17.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好 好 好\N{\rEng}Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.74,1:06:37.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他去便利店了 一会儿就回来\N{\rEng}He'll be back with some groceries.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.49,1:06:43.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要不今晚一起烤棉花糖？\N{\rEng}Then, how about tonight, we do some s'mores in the fireplace?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.36,1:06:44.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,随便\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.60,1:06:47.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.37,1:06:51.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他是不是跟你说闹鬼的事了？\N{\rEng}Was he blabbing to you about his ghosts?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.08,1:06:54.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阁楼里闹鬼的事？\N{\rEng}The ones that live in the cupola?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.90,1:06:56.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是呀\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.64,1:06:59.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是真的吗？\N{\rEng}Well, are there?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.07,1:07:02.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你说呢？\N{\rEng}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.42,1:07:05.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别太信你阿爷\N{\rEng}I wouldn't pay too much attention to Zaydee.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.08,1:07:11.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他人不错 就是有时喝得太多\N{\rEng}He's a good man. But, sometimes, well, sometimes, he drinks too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.63,1:07:14.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,喝多了就会天马行空 你懂他那一套\N{\rEng}Then he rides his hobby horses. I'm sure you know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.80,1:07:18.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,杰弗里家男孩是谁？\N{\rEng}Who was the Jefferies boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.40,1:07:26.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧 小宝 那是件让人心酸的事\N{\rEng}Well...that was a very sad thing, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.37,1:07:28.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他住旁边那巷子\N{\rEng}He lived on the next block over,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.80,1:07:34.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,追球追到马路上结果被车撞了\N{\rEng}and he got hit by a car when he chased a ball into the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.33,1:07:37.81,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那是很久前的事儿了\N{\rEng}It happened a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.68,1:07:45.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是你爷爷说他提前见过那一幕 他并没有\N{\rEng}And if your grandpa says he saw it before it happened, he's mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.38,1:07:51.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那只是他酒后乱说\N{\rEng}He just drinks too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.61,1:08:05.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要不我帮你送到史坦利奶奶那儿？\N{\rEng}You know, I could take those to Mrs. Stanley if you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.31,1:08:09.90,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哎呀 你真贴心 维拉看到你肯定特开心\N{\rEng}Oh, that's very thoughtful of you. I bet Vera'd love that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.89,1:08:13.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,简直绝了\N{\rEng}Just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.50,1:08:15.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你奶奶真是个烘焙大师\N{\rEng}Your, your grandmother is an artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.54,1:08:18.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢谢你带来 你主动要来送的吧？\N{\rEng}Thank you for bringing them over. Was that your idea?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.33,1:08:20.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-说实话哦 -是的\N{\rEng}-Be honest. -It was.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.07,1:08:22.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要喝茶吗？\N{\rEng}Well, can I make you a cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.72,1:08:27.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,其实我不喝茶 有杯牛奶就完美了\N{\rEng}Um, I don't drink tea, but, um, I wouldn't mind a glass of milk.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.67,1:08:31.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你奶奶真是个大好人\N{\rEng}Well, your grandmother's a saint.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.13,1:08:32.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你爷爷呢？\N{\rEng}And what about your granddad?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.47,1:08:34.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他背上那东西去检查了吗？\N{\rEng}Did he have that thing on his back looked at?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.68,1:08:37.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯 医生拿掉了 还做了化验\N{\rEng}Yeah, the, the doctor took it off and had it tested.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.17,1:08:38.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,全告诉我\N{\rEng}Tell me everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.87,1:08:41.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不是坏的那种\N{\rEng}It wasn't one of the bad ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.57,1:08:43.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢天谢地\N{\rEng}Thank God for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.31,1:08:44.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.88,1:08:52.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他跟奶奶聊那个叫亨利·彼得森的人\N{\rEng}He, um, he was talking to Grandma about someone named Henry Peterson.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.62,1:08:53.91,Default-1,,0,0,0,,太惨了\N{\rEng}So awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.93,1:08:57.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亨利跟你爷爷一样是管账的\N{\rEng}You know, Henry was a bookkeeper, just like your granddad.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.37,1:09:00.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还接了镇上你阿爷扛不下的活儿...\N{\rEng}He did a lot of the other businesses in town. The ones that your Zaydee didn't do...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.78,1:09:03.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到底怎么回事？\N{\rEng}How did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.69,1:09:06.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这种事你还是别听了\N{\rEng}I don't think you want to hear about that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.77,1:09:11.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,呃 爷爷说 说那很平和\N{\rEng}Um, w-w-well, Granddad said it was, uh, peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.57,1:09:13.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,平和？\N{\rEng}Peaceful?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.29,1:09:16.19,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他自尽了 上吊的\N{\rEng}He killed himself. Hung himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.21,1:09:19.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他老婆跟个刚满十八的小伙子私奔了\N{\rEng}His wife, you see, she ran off with this younger man, barely old enough to vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.91,1:09:23.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她自己都四十多了 你怎么看？\N{\rEng}And she was in her 40s. What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.48,1:09:25.03,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-天哪 -对 可不是\N{\rEng}-Wow. -Damn right, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.05,1:09:28.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我还听说...\N{\rEng}And then, I heard that...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.02,1:09:36.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,学校那边有什么新鲜事？\N{\rEng}What's happening at school?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.20,1:09:38.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谁和谁在亲亲啦？\N{\rEng}Who's smooching who?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.50,1:09:43.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,放心说吧 无人能闻得见 我只多留片刻\N{\rEng}"Talk honestly, for no one else hears you and I stay only a minute longer."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.80,1:09:46.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我是否自相矛盾？\N{\rEng}"Do I contradict myself?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.81,1:09:51.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我就自相矛盾\N{\rEng}"Very well then, I contradict myself,"
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.59,1:09:56.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我心疆无限 我包罗万象\N{\rEng}"I am large. I contain multitudes."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.03,1:09:58.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,六年级的最后一堂课上\N{\rEng}On the last day of sixth grade,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.34,1:10:04.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那位小清新气息 管不住课堂的理查兹老师\N{\rEng}Miss Richards, a sweet, hippie-dippyish young woman who had no command of discipline
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.56,1:10:09.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,怕是很快就要被劝退\N{\rEng}and would probably not last long in the public education system,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.44,1:10:17.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还是在查克班上照念惠特曼《自我之歌》的诗\N{\rEng}tried to recite for Chuck's class some verse of Walt Whitman's "Song of Myself."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.79,1:10:21.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,若最初寻我不得 莫失信心\N{\rEng}"Failing to fetch me at first keep encouraged.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.28,1:10:25.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,错过此处 再觅它方\N{\rEng}Missing me one place, search another."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.33,1:10:40.14,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这节课还算顺利 对吧？\N{\rEng}That went well, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.16,1:10:43.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯 让您为难了\N{\rEng}Yeah, I'm, I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.39,1:10:54.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,惠特曼那句“我心疆无限 我包罗万象”是啥意思？\N{\rEng}What does he mean when he says, "I am large, I contain multitudes"?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.40,1:10:56.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你觉得他想表达什么？\N{\rEng}What do you think he means?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.75,1:10:59.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,包罗他认识的所有人\N{\rEng}All the people he knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.11,1:11:00.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.88,1:11:04.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但也许不止于此\N{\rEng}But maybe he means even more.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.08,1:11:07.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来 过来\N{\rEng}Here. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.32,1:11:11.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我的两手之间 那里有什么？\N{\rEng}What's in there? Between my hands?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.81,1:11:13.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我头\N{\rEng}My brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.59,1:11:16.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不 不是这个意思\N{\rEng}No, um, that's not exactly what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.81,1:11:22.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我是说 在我两手之间 里面装的是什么\N{\rEng}What's in there? Right between my hands right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.03,1:11:23.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.20,1:11:26.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,里面有你认识的所有人吗？\N{\rEng}All the people you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.28,1:11:27.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有吧\N{\rEng}I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.82,1:11:31.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就只有你认识的人吗？\N{\rEng}Just the people you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.80,1:11:36.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,里面是你见过的记住的一切\N{\rEng}Everything you see. Everything you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.48,1:11:38.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是整个世界 查克\N{\rEng}The world, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.59,1:11:41.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,天上的飞机 地上的井盖\N{\rEng}Planes in the sky. Manhole covers in the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.31,1:11:44.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,年复一年 你脑海中的世界\N{\rEng}Every year that you live, that world inside your head
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.45,1:11:49.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,会越来越大 越鲜明 越丰富 越复杂\N{\rEng}will get bigger and brighter and more detailed and complex.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.15,1:11:52.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你会在脑海中构建城市 国家 大陆\N{\rEng}You will build cities and countries and continents,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.80,1:11:57.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,并用真实和想象的人去充实那里\N{\rEng}and you will fill them with people and faces, real and imagined.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.67,1:12:00.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,明白了吗？\N{\rEng}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.09,1:12:01.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别就此止步\N{\rEng}Don't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.81,1:12:06.24,Default-1,,0,0,0,,把你见过的 认识的\N{\rEng}You fill the whole thing with everyone you ever meet,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.27,1:12:11.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,甚至想象的每个人都给装进去\N{\rEng}everyone you ever know, everyone you ever just imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.78,1:12:14.76,Default-1,,0,0,0,,它就变成了个小宇宙\N{\rEng}It'll be a universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.78,1:12:20.33,Default-1,,0,0,0,,整个宇宙就在我两手之间\N{\rEng}A whole universe right between my hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.35,1:12:25.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你能包罗万象\N{\rEng}You contain multitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.18,1:12:27.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.01,1:12:33.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那个宇宙会怎样 要是有人\N{\rEng}what happens to that universe if someone...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.28,1:12:35.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,比如说\N{\rEng}I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.46,1:12:41.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在冰面上打滑 冲下高架桥 或者\N{\rEng}hits a patch of ice and goes off an overpass or...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.94,1:12:44.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别太纠结这些\N{\rEng}Don't worry too much about those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.81,1:12:50.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,只要记住 你包罗万象 查克\N{\rEng}Just remember that you contain multitudes, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.34,1:12:53.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这多棒啊\N{\rEng}Isn't that wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.17,1:12:56.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好了 就这样 你真是个好孩子\N{\rEng}Now, go on. You were such a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.48,1:13:00.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,能教你我很开心\N{\rEng}I've really enjoyed having you in class.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.15,1:13:24.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克暑假本来过得挺好 直到八月\N{\rEng}Chuck did enjoy his summer until August,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.46,1:13:27.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他阿奶去世了\N{\rEng}when Bubbie died.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.40,1:13:33.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事情发生在街角的便利店里\N{\rEng}It happened at the grocery store down the street,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.43,1:13:37.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,公开场合 有点不太体面\N{\rEng}in public, which was a little undignified,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.17,1:13:41.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,至少这种死法能让人安心地说...\N{\rEng}but at least it was the kind of death where people can safely say...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.28,1:13:44.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,幸好她一生没受什么罪\N{\rEng}Thank God she didn't suffer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.09,1:13:45.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,至于那句...\N{\rEng}The other standby...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.58,1:13:47.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她一生又长又圆满\N{\rEng}She had a long, full life.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.41,1:13:50.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就说不准了\N{\rEng}...was more of a gray area.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.18,1:13:54.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,毕竟她才六十多岁\N{\rEng}Sarah Krantz had yet to reach her mid-60s.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.03,1:14:03.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,又一次 家里再次陷入彻底的悲伤\N{\rEng}Once more, the house on Pilchard Street was one of unadulterated sadness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.11,1:14:07.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比戴上了黑纱 越发消瘦\N{\rEng}Albie wore his mourning band, and lost weight,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.83,1:14:10.22,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也不再讲笑话了\N{\rEng}and stopped telling his jokes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.24,1:14:14.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,比他实际七十岁还显老\N{\rEng}and began to look older than his 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.35,1:14:24.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-就买这点？ -嗯\N{\rEng}-That's it? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.39,1:14:26.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一块七毛五\N{\rEng}Buck 75.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.39,1:14:35.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几周前来的那个女士 就是后来去世的那位\N{\rEng}Um, that lady who was in here a few weeks ago, the one who died.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.36,1:14:38.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事情发生在哪儿？\N{\rEng}Where was she when it happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.80,1:14:42.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小朋友 这话题有点吓人\N{\rEng}That's a little creepy, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.41,1:14:45.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她是我奶奶\N{\rEng}She was my grandma.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.02,1:14:48.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她当时想拿面包\N{\rEng}She was getting a loaf of bread.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.08,1:14:52.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,结果把整排货架都拽倒砸她身上了\N{\rEng}Pulled down almost everything on the shelf when she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.64,1:14:57.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是我说多了 你别介意\N{\rEng}I'm sorry if that's too much information.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.77,1:14:59.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\rEng}Nah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.51,1:15:03.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我早知道了\N{\rEng}I already knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.44,1:16:00.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-别！ -啥？\N{\rEng}-No! -What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.18,1:16:05.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-走开 快走开 -等下\N{\rEng}-Get away from there! You get away from there. -What? Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.09,1:16:30.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,把锁给我\N{\rEng}Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.38,1:16:32.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,给我 给我\N{\rEng}Give it to me. Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.95,1:16:36.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,抓紧给我\N{\rEng}Give me it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.59,1:16:42.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 对不起\N{\rEng}Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.44,1:16:44.03,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\rEng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.05,1:16:45.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你没受伤吧\N{\rEng}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.89,1:16:48.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你看到了什么？\N{\rEng}What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.50,1:16:51.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到底看到了什么？\N{\rEng}What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.67,1:16:55.61,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对不起 你不能去那里\N{\rEng}I'm sorry. It's just, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.63,1:16:58.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,绝不能去那里 小查\N{\rEng}You can't do that, Chucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.59,1:17:00.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,绝不能\N{\rEng}You just can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.28,1:17:02.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 我真对不起\N{\rEng}Oh, I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.13,1:17:08.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 对不起 真的 真是对不起\N{\rEng}Oh, I'm sorry. I'm so, so sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.43,1:17:21.79,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,15)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5\fsp2\i1}课后兴趣班纳新
